559
00:27:30.500 --> 00:27:32.510
I have to rescue that jackass?!

560
00:27:32.510 --> 00:27:34.590
Focus, Swirly-phim!

561
00:27:34.590 --> 00:27:36.340
This is serious!

562
00:27:42.850 --> 00:27:44.390
I've been meaning...

563
00:27:44.890 --> 00:27:49.860
to settle the score with you eventually...

564
00:27:52.400 --> 00:27:54.150
Sorry to keep you waiting!

565
00:27:54.150 --> 00:27:55.900
Roronoa!

566
00:27:57.110 --> 00:27:59.990
Huh?! Why does he look like that?

567
00:27:59.990 --> 00:28:04.120
It's supposed to be a giraffe,
but it looks different than last time.

568
00:28:04.120 --> 00:28:08.330
Well, it'll look like a corpse
after I cut it either way.

569
00:28:08.330 --> 00:28:10.460
I'd like to see you try...

570
00:28:10.460 --> 00:28:11.710
Roronoa!

571
00:28:12.750 --> 00:28:14.760
Look after the ship, Brook!

572
00:28:14.760 --> 00:28:15.720
Okay!

573
00:28:15.720 --> 00:28:17.090
Get ready for this!

574
00:28:17.090 --> 00:28:18.430
Nose Pistol!

575
00:28:23.720 --> 00:28:26.680
This is only a taste of what's to come!

576
00:28:26.680 --> 00:28:28.650
Kiliman-Gyro!

577
00:28:30.610 --> 00:28:32.980
It's not over yet!

578
00:28:45.790 --> 00:28:48.000
I got more than enough experience...

579
00:28:48.540 --> 00:28:52.210
fighting snakes back in Wano!

580
00:28:52.840 --> 00:28:56.420
I'm sick of it!

581
00:29:12.730 --> 00:29:15.110
Now, before Vegapunk comes out...

582
00:29:15.690 --> 00:29:17.650
destroy the lab!

583
00:29:35.710 --> 00:29:38.010
Not good! They're going to destroy the lab!

584
00:29:57.480 --> 00:29:58.820
This is bad!

585
00:29:58.820 --> 00:30:01.450
If we don't do something,
we'll be destroyed, too!

586
00:30:01.450 --> 00:30:02.280
What?!

587
00:30:24.800 --> 00:30:25.760
Everyone!

588
00:30:26.850 --> 00:30:28.600
In this situation...

589
00:30:28.600 --> 00:30:30.310
you have no chance of winning!

590
00:30:30.930 --> 00:30:32.060
Whoa, hey!

591
00:30:32.060 --> 00:30:33.850
You guys are showboating!

592
00:30:34.350 --> 00:30:35.770
Damn!

593
00:30:44.360 --> 00:30:47.580
Finish the mission just like that!

594
00:31:00.420 --> 00:31:01.550
What?!

595
00:31:02.380 --> 00:31:04.130
You...

596
00:31:18.520 --> 00:31:19.650
Kaku!

597
00:31:23.490 --> 00:31:24.950
What are you doing?!

598
00:31:26.740 --> 00:31:28.240
Stussy!

599
00:31:30.120 --> 00:31:31.790
What am I doing?

600
00:31:32.660 --> 00:31:34.540
I just put him to sleep.

601
00:31:38.920 --> 00:31:40.840
Please, Lucci...

602
00:31:42.050 --> 00:31:43.970
Won't you fall asleep, too?

603
00:31:45.970 --> 00:31:49.220
Stussy
MADS Clone Experiment
First Successful Subject
Modeled After
Miss Buckingham Stussy
of the Rocks Pirates

604
00:31:49.220 --> 00:31:53.140
A Stretch of Sea
in the New World

605
00:32:08.610 --> 00:32:11.370
That fish was insanely huge!

606
00:32:11.370 --> 00:32:14.120
It's not really a normal sea.

607
00:32:14.870 --> 00:32:16.370
I'm excited.

608
00:32:17.170 --> 00:32:18.670
Is that an island?

609
00:32:19.920 --> 00:32:21.340
Kid, wake up!

610
00:32:22.460 --> 00:32:23.630
We spotted land.

611
00:32:24.130 --> 00:32:25.510
Should we check it out?

612
00:32:26.380 --> 00:32:28.380
Why are you asking that?

613
00:32:28.380 --> 00:32:32.600
We shouldn't be hesitating
to land anywhere anymore.

614
00:32:34.100 --> 00:32:36.600
Hey, what's that?

615
00:32:39.940 --> 00:32:44.780
That island must be the home of the giants.

616
00:32:45.400 --> 00:32:46.780
It's Elbaph!

617
00:32:49.030 --> 00:32:51.120
Elbaph...

618
00:32:51.120 --> 00:32:53.370
Marine Headquarters
G-14 Branch

619
00:32:53.370 --> 00:32:56.080
Give me a break, Vice Admiral Garp!

620
00:32:56.500 --> 00:33:00.330
We're planning to leave for Egghead soon.

621
00:33:00.330 --> 00:33:02.210
Don't take any of my troops away!

622
00:33:02.210 --> 00:33:04.880
Lighten up, Doll!

623
00:33:07.590 --> 00:33:09.590
What's so funny?!

624
00:33:09.590 --> 00:33:13.720
Besides, if you're gonna attack
an island occupied by an Emperor,

625
00:33:13.720 --> 00:33:15.560
that means you got permission

626
00:33:15.560 --> 00:33:17.520
from the brass, right?!

627
00:33:17.520 --> 00:33:18.520
What?

628
00:33:18.520 --> 00:33:19.480
Why would I?

629
00:33:20.940 --> 00:33:23.310
How many decades have you been a Marine?!

630
00:33:25.570 --> 00:33:27.280
Don't worry about it.

631
00:33:27.280 --> 00:33:28.900
I'm already here anyway.

632
00:33:28.900 --> 00:33:30.400
"Here"?!

633
00:33:32.070 --> 00:33:34.200
Helmeppo!

634
00:33:34.200 --> 00:33:36.950
Come on out!

635
00:33:37.700 --> 00:33:38.410
What is it?

636
00:33:39.040 --> 00:33:40.160
Is it a pirate?!

637
00:33:40.160 --> 00:33:42.540
Did they call Helmeppo out to kill him?!

638
00:33:42.540 --> 00:33:44.420
No! That's...

639
00:33:52.260 --> 00:33:53.760
Helmeppo!

640
00:33:53.760 --> 00:33:55.470
There you are!

641
00:33:55.850 --> 00:33:57.810
Vice Admiral Garp!

642
00:33:59.480 --> 00:34:01.230
I'm so happy to see you!

643
00:34:01.230 --> 00:34:03.230
Koby...

644
00:34:03.230 --> 00:34:04.810
He got caught...

645
00:34:04.810 --> 00:34:07.780
by Blackbeard...

646
00:34:08.150 --> 00:34:11.780
I couldn't do anything!

647
00:34:11.780 --> 00:34:14.160
Stop crying!

648
00:34:14.160 --> 00:34:15.580
How pathetic!

649
00:34:17.490 --> 00:34:19.410
Vice Admiral Garp!

650
00:34:20.500 --> 00:34:22.210
Now then...

651
00:34:22.210 --> 00:34:23.920
get on board!

652
00:34:24.380 --> 00:34:28.250
We're heading to the Pirate Island, Beehive,

653
00:34:28.250 --> 00:34:30.630
to beat the hell out of some pirates...

654
00:34:30.970 --> 00:34:33.380
and rescue...

655
00:34:33.380 --> 00:34:35.340
Captain Koby!

656
00:34:35.720 --> 00:34:37.850
– Vice Admiral Garp!
– Vice Admiral Garp!
